Use only MCP tools. No Python code.

Objective: Map Tests and Test Steps to User Stories

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 1 — READ BOTH FILES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Use the filesystem MCP tool to read these two files
from the Testable_PoC project folder:

  File 1: test-cases-review-compliance.md
          → Contains: TC ID, Title, Description, Priority
          → Used to create JIRA Test issues

  File 2: test-steps-compliance.csv
          → Contains: TC ID, Summary, Step, Action, Data,
                       Expected Result
          → Used to import steps into each Test issue via Xray

Parse and map every TC ID from File 1 to its matching
rows in File 2 before proceeding.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 2 — CREATE JIRA TEST ISSUES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
For each test case in test-cases-review-<name>.md,
use the createJiraIssue MCP tool to create an issue:

  Project    : TP
  Issue Type : Test
  Priority   : Medium
  Summary    : <TC Title from md file — exact as written>
  Description: <TC Description from md file>
               Do NOT include Expected Result in description.
               Description is a one-line summary only.
  Labels     : regression

After each issue is created:
  Save the mapping → TC-001 : TP-90
                     TC-002 : TP-91
                     TC-003 : TP-92
                     (continue for all)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 3 — IMPORT TEST STEPS FROM CSV
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
For each JIRA Test issue created in Step 2,
use the fetchAtlassian MCP tool to POST each step
to the Xray REST API.

For every step row in test-steps-<name>.csv
where the TC ID matches the JIRA issue:

  Method  : POST
  URL     : https://testable.atlassian.net/rest/raven/1.0/api/test/{issueKey}/step
  Headers : Content-Type: application/json
  Body    :
  {
    "index"  : <Step number from CSV>,
    "step"   : "<Action column from CSV>",
    "data"   : "<Data column from CSV>",
    "result" : "<Expected Result column from CSV>"
  }

RULES:
  - Call this API once per step row — not once per test case
  - Expected Result goes ONLY into the "result" field
  - Expected Result must NOT be in description or step field
  - If Data column is empty, send "data": ""
  - Process all steps in order (Step 1 before Step 2, etc.)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
STEP 4 — MAP ALL TESTS TO TP-51
        UNDER TEST COVERAGE ONLY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
After ALL issues and steps are created,
use the fetchAtlassian MCP tool to call the Xray REST API:

  Method  : PUT
  URL     : https://testable.atlassian.net/rest/raven/1.0/api/testcase/TP-51/test
  Headers : Content-Type: application/json
  Body    :
  {
    "add": [<every JIRA key created in Step 2>]
  }

STRICT RULES:
  - Do NOT use createIssueLink
  - Do NOT add as backlog items or linked work items
  - Tests must appear ONLY under
    TP-51 → Test Coverage → Add Tests
  - No other association should be created

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
